OL,3,CStarmer refuses to rule out benefits
OL,4,Ccuts for many disabled people
OL,6,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer has
OL,7,Frefused to rule out benefits cuts for
OL,8,Fmany disabled people when asked
OL,9,Fdirectly about changes to the benefits
OL,10,Fsystem.
OL,12,FLiberal Democrat leader Ed Davey asked
OL,13,Fthe PM directly if he would "calm
OL,14,Fanxieties that disability benefits for
OL,15,Fpeople that simply can't work will not
OL,16,Fbe cut", to which Starmer replied "we
OL,17,Fwill of course support those who need
OL,18,Fsupport".
